title: JUI-P Ghulam Dastagir Badeni wins PB-34 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI-P) candidate Ghulam Dastagir Badeni has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-34, Nushki by securing 16,771 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was BNP candidate Muhammad Raheem who bagged 15,014 votes.
Voters turnout remained 41.79 percent.
